            reversedMeaning: "The recognition you sought has not arrived, or victory has come without the acknowledgment you needed to make it feel real. The crowd is silent. Examine whether the validation was necessary, and whether the achievement holds meaning in its own right.",
            keywords: ["victory", "recognition", "achievement", "public success"],
            symbolism: "A triumphant rider on a white horse bears a laurel wreath aloft, accompanied by a procession of supporters.",
            symbolName: "flame"),
        TarotCard(id: 28, name: "Seven of Wands", arcana: .minor, suit: .wands, number: "7",
            uprightMeaning: "You have claimed the high ground and they are coming for it. The Seven of Wands calls for the courage to defend what you have built, to hold your position against the critics, challengers, and competitors who see your advantage as something to be taken. Advantageous positions require active defence.",
