            keywords: ["speed", "momentum", "communication", "swift action"],
            symbolism: "Eight parallel wands sail across a clear sky toward a green landscape — pure directed motion with nothing to impede it.",
            symbolName: "flame"),
        TarotCard(id: 30, name: "Nine of Wands", arcana: .minor, suit: .wands, number: "9",
            uprightMeaning: "Wounded but undefeated. The weary guardian leans on his wand, eight more standing behind him, having endured battle after battle. The resilience of this card is not the buoyancy of the untested but the harder, deeper steadfastness of the one who has seen difficulty and chosen to stand regardless.",
            reversedMeaning: "Stubbornness has replaced resilience. You have fought so long that fighting has become an identity, and you are now defending positions that no longer need defending. Or exhaustion has finally overwhelmed the will, and rest is not defeat but survival.",
            keywords: ["resilience", "perseverance", "courage", "close to the goal"],
            symbolism: "A battered sentinel stands guard before eight upright wands, head bandaged, eyes alert — the look of one who has survived what should have broken them.",
