        TarotCard(id: 31, name: "Ten of Wands", arcana: .minor, suit: .wands, number: "10",
            uprightMeaning: "The figure is almost bent double beneath the ten wands he carries, yet the destination is visible just ahead. The Ten of Wands speaks of taking on too much and the burning need to either distribute the burden or set some of it down. The strength to carry is admirable; the wisdom to delegate is mastery.",
            reversedMeaning: "The burden has become unbearable, and either collapse is imminent or relief is finally arriving through the willingness to let go of unnecessary weight. Some of what you carry was never yours to carry. Asking for help is not weakness — it is the prerequisite of sustainability.",
